Introduction

Base URL: http://example-test.laravel.com

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is authenticated using a Bearer token.

Send your token in the Authorization header:

Authorization: Bearer <token>

You can retrieve the token by calling the login endpoint (POST /api/login).

Endpoints

用户登录接口

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"stoltenberg.stanley@example.com\",
    \"password\": \"voluptatem\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "stoltenberg.stanley@example.com",
    "password": "voluptatem"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/login

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

email   string   

Must be a valid email address. Example: stoltenberg.stanley@example.com

password   string   

Example: voluptatem

用户登出接口

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/logout" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/logout"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/me" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/me"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (401):

content-type: application/json
access-control-allow-origin: *

创建新用户

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/users" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"zoqnfj\",
    \"email\": \"iherman@example.com\",
    \"password\": \"!k%mQT+w{g^|C-W2+)N<\",
    \"phone\": \"auihxq\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/users"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "zoqnfj",
    "email": "iherman@example.com",
    "password": "!k%mQT+w{g^|C-W2+)N<",
    "phone": "auihxq"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/users

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: zoqnfj

email   string   

Must be a valid email address. Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: iherman@example.com

password   string   

Must be at least 8 characters. Example: !k%mQT+w{g^|C-W2+)N<

phone   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 20 characters. Example: auihxq

roles   string[]  optional  

The id of an existing record in the roles table.

更新用户信息

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request PUT \
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/users/aut" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"uwbcijcms\",
    \"password\": \")|m]+r3r.xWv8o\",
    \"phone\": \"skafxvdqnp\",
    \"is_active\": true
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/users/aut"
);

const headers = {

Request

PATCH api/users/{id}

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

URL Parameters

id   string   

The ID of the user. Example: aut

Body Parameters

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: uwbcijcms

email   string  optional  
password   string  optional  

Must be at least 8 characters. Example: )|m]+r3r.xWv8o

phone   string  optional  

Must not be greater than 20 characters. Example: skafxvdqnp

is_active   boolean  optional  

Example: true

roles   string[]  optional  

The id of an existing record in the roles table.

    --header "Accept: application/json"

);

创建新角色

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/roles" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"lrgomrfqkfrfqjxc\",
    \"slug\": \"nqptvps\",
    \"description\": \"Distinctio et culpa ut et voluptas aliquam.\",
    \"is_active\": true
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/roles"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "lrgomrfqkfrfqjxc",
    "slug": "nqptvps",
    "description": "Distinctio et culpa ut et voluptas aliquam.",
    "is_active": true
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/work-orders/aut" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/work-orders/aut"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (401):

Show headers 
cache-control: no-cache, private
content-type: application/json
access-control-allow-origin: *
 

{
    "success": false,
    "code": 401,
    "message": "未授权，请先登录"
}
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

URL Parameters

id   string   

The ID of the work order. Example: aut

更新工单信息

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request PUT \
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/work-orders/accusamus" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"product_id\": \"dolores\",
    \"warehouse_id\": \"officia\",
    \"quantity\": 18,
    \"start_date\": \"2025-12-24T06:40:50\",
    \"planned_end_date\": \"2047-05-27\",
    \"remark\": \"amet\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/work-orders/accusamus"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "product_id": "dolores",
    "warehouse_id": "officia",
    "quantity": 18,
    "start_date": "2025-12-24T06:40:50",
    "planned_end_date": "2047-05-27",
    "remark": "amet"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "PUT",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

PUT api/work-orders/{id}

PATCH api/work-orders/{id}

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

URL Parameters

id   string   

The ID of the work order. Example: accusamus

Body Parameters

product_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the products table. Example: dolores

bom_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the boms table.

process_route_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the process_routes table.

warehouse_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the warehouses table. Example: officia

quantity   integer   

Must be at least 1. Example: 18

start_date   string   

Must be a valid date. Example: 2025-12-24T06:40:50

planned_end_date   string   

Must be a valid date. Must be a date after start_date. Example: 2047-05-27

assigned_to   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the users table.

remark   string  optional  

Example: amet

Request      

POST api/work-orders/{id}/issue-material

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

URL Parameters

id   string   

The ID of the work order. Example: vitae

Body Parameters

items   object[]   

Must have at least 1 items.
product_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the products table. Example: officia

quantity   integer   

Must be at least 1. Example: 66

location_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the warehouse_locations table.

创建生产报工单

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/production-reports" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"work_order_id\": \"quod\",
    \"report_date\": \"2025-12-24T06:40:50\",
    \"quantity\": 80,
    \"qualified_quantity\": 24,
    \"defective_quantity\": 57,
    \"work_hours\": 33,
    \"overtime_hours\": 89,
    \"remark\": \"soluta\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/production-reports"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "work_order_id": "quod",
    "report_date": "2025-12-24T06:40:50",
    "quantity": 80,
    "qualified_quantity": 24,
    "defective_quantity": 57,
    "work_hours": 33,
    "overtime_hours": 89,
    "remark": "soluta"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Request      

POST api/production-reports

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

work_order_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the work_orders table. Example: quod

work_order_item_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the work_order_items table.

report_date   string   

Must be a valid date. Example: 2025-12-24T06:40:50

quantity   integer   

Must be at least 1. Example: 80

qualified_quantity   integer  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 24

defective_quantity   integer  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 57

work_hours   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 33

overtime_hours   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 89

remark   string  optional  

Example: soluta

POST api/accounts-payable

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

supplier_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the suppliers table. Example: amet

reference_type   string  optional  

Example: neque

reference_id   integer  optional  

Example: 8

reference_no   string  optional  

Example: corporis

invoice_date   string   

Must be a valid date. Example: 2025-12-24T06:40:50

due_date   string   

Must be a valid date. Must be a date after invoice_date. Example: 2106-05-02

original_amount   number   

Must be at least 0. Example: 84

paid_amount   number  optional  

Must be at least 0. Example: 50

currency_id   string  optional  

The id of an existing record in the currencies table.

remark   string  optional  

Example: natus

  • end

  • any

    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"uqfcfzczkpcpbxevs\",
    \"code\": \"illum\",
    \"category\": \"custom\",
    \"description\": \"Non tempora sit dolor nulla autem voluptate repellat.\",
    \"query_config\": [],
    \"display_config\": [],
    \"is_active\": true
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/custom-reports"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "uqfcfzczkpcpbxevs",
    "code": "illum",
    "category": "custom",
    "description": "Non tempora sit dolor nulla autem voluptate repellat.",
    "query_config": [],
    "display_config": [],
    "is_active": true
};

    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"user_id\": \"quisquam\",
    \"type\": \"system\",
    \"title\": \"eqoex\",
    \"content\": \"voluptatibus\",
    \"channel\": \"email\",
    \"priority\": \"low\",
    \"reference_type\": \"qui\",
    \"reference_id\": 20,
    \"reference_no\": \"temporibus\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://example-test.laravel.com/api/notifications/send"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "user_id": "quisquam",
    "type": "system",
    "title": "eqoex",
    "content": "voluptatibus",
    "channel": "email",
    "priority": "low",
    "reference_type": "qui",
    "reference_id": 20,
    "reference_no": "temporibus"
};

    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Request      

POST api/notifications/send

Headers

Authorization      

Example: Bearer Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN}

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

user_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the users table. Example: quisquam

type   string   

Example: system

Must be one of:
  • system
  • approval
  • order
  • inventory
  • financial
title   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: eqoex

content   string   

Example: voluptatibus

channel   string  optional  

Example: email

Must be one of:
  • system
  • email
  • sms
  • push
priority   string  optional  

Example: low

Must be one of:
  • low
  • normal
  • high
  • urgent
reference_type   string  optional  

Example: qui

reference_id   integer  optional  

Example: 20

reference_no   string  optional  

Example: temporibus

data   object  optional
